description: The exciting conclusion of Captain Gravity and the Power of the Vril finds Joshua plummeting toward the earth in psychological chaos. Not only does his body fight the extreme cold of the atmosphere, but his mind battles startling visions of the Vril's potential, visions that hold clues for defeating the demonic Jaeger, visions of ancient Atlantis. But Joshua must survive his fall and a brutal submarine battle in order to save Chase and the world from Jaeger's maniacal designs.

volume.name: Captain Gravity And The Power Of Vril

description: In true adventure serial style, Penny-Farthing presents the debut of Captain Marvelous! But how can a celluloid hero be real? It's a reality Joshua Jone, a.k.a. Captain Gravity, has to struggle with as his childhood hero arrives on the scene. How do you define the word Hero? Perhaps after this issue you'll know. Join us for a super-power blow out where only one Captain can rise above it all.

This promotional comic book starts off with an exciting intergalactic chase.  A specialized team of agents are on the heels of capturing their sole target -- the destroyer of their homeworld.  Their pursuit eventually leads them to a 9 planet solar system.  There, they find that the criminal lands on the third planet from the sun and plans on conquering it as well.  The team makes Earth their new home, and vows to protect it from the same fate their home planet suffered.
name: More Trouble Than You Can Fathom!
